  "root_text": {
    "an4.42:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4.42 ",
    "an4.42:0.2": "5. Rohitassavagga ",
    "an4.42:0.3": "Pañhabyākaraṇasutta ",
    "an4.42:1.1": "“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, pañhabyākaraṇāni. ",
    "an4.42:1.2": "Katamāni cattāri? ",
    "an4.42:1.3": "Atthi, bhikkhave, pañho ekaṁsabyākaraṇīyo; ",
    "an4.42:1.4": "atthi, bhikkhave, pañho vibhajjabyākaraṇīyo; ",
    "an4.42:1.5": "atthi, bhikkhave, pañho paṭipucchābyākaraṇīyo; ",
    "an4.42:1.6": "atthi, bhikkhave, pañho ṭhapanīyo. ",
    "an4.42:1.7": "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri pañhabyākaraṇānīti. ",
    "an4.42:2.1": "Ekaṁsavacanaṁ ekaṁ, ",
    "an4.42:2.2": "vibhajjavacanāparaṁ; ",
    "an4.42:2.3": "Tatiyaṁ paṭipuccheyya, ",
    "an4.42:2.4": "catutthaṁ pana ṭhāpaye. ",
    "an4.42:3.1": "Yo ca tesaṁ tattha tattha, ",
    "an4.42:3.2": "jānāti anudhammataṁ; ",
    "an4.42:3.3": "Catupañhassa kusalo, ",
    "an4.42:3.4": "āhu bhikkhuṁ tathāvidhaṁ. ",
    "an4.42:4.1": "Durāsado duppasaho, ",
    "an4.42:4.2": "gambhīro duppadhaṁsiyo; ",
    "an4.42:4.3": "Atho atthe anatthe ca, ",
    "an4.42:4.4": "ubhayassa hoti kovido. ",
    "an4.42:5.1": "Anatthaṁ parivajjeti, ",
    "an4.42:5.2": "atthaṁ gaṇhāti paṇḍito; ",
    "an4.42:5.3": "Atthābhisamayā dhīro, ",
    "an4.42:5.4": "paṇḍitoti pavuccatī”ti. ",
    "an4.42:5.5": "Dutiyaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an4.42:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 4.42 ",
    "an4.42:0.2": "5. With Rohitassa ",
    "an4.42:0.3": "Ways of Answering Questions ",
    "an4.42:1.1": "“Mendicants, there are these four ways of answering questions. ",
    "an4.42:1.2": "What four? ",
    "an4.42:1.3": "There is a question that should be answered categorically. ",
    "an4.42:1.4": "There is a question that should be answered analytically. ",
    "an4.42:1.5": "There is a question that should be answered with a counter-question. ",
    "an4.42:1.6": "There is a question that should be set aside. ",
    "an4.42:1.7": "These are the four ways of answering questions. ",
    "an4.42:2.1": "One is stated categorically, ",
    "an4.42:2.2": "another analytically, ",
    "an4.42:2.3": "a third with a counter-question, ",
    "an4.42:2.4": "while a fourth is set aside. ",
    "an4.42:3.1": "That sort of mendicant, <j>who knows each of these, ",
    "an4.42:3.2": "in line with good principles, ",
    "an4.42:3.3": "is said to be skilled ",
    "an4.42:3.4": "in the four kinds of questions. ",
    "an4.42:4.1": "They’re intimidating, hard to defeat, ",
    "an4.42:4.2": "deep, and hard to crush. ",
    "an4.42:4.3": "They’re expert in both ",
    "an4.42:4.4": "what the meaning is and what it isn’t. ",
    "an4.42:5.1": "Shunning what is not the meaning, ",
    "an4.42:5.2": "an astute person grasps the meaning. ",
    "an4.42:5.3": "An attentive one, comprehending the meaning, ",
    "an4.42:5.4": "is said to be astute.” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "an4.42:1.1": "pañhabyākaraṇāni → pañhābyākaraṇāni (mr) ",
    "an4.42:3.1": "tesaṁ → nesaṁ (bj, sya-all, km) ",
    "an4.42:4.4": "ubhayassa hoti kovido → ubhayatthassa kovido (sya-all, km) "
  },
